main event: A female civilian reported an unusual aircraft sighting over Long Island on March 17, 1950, describing it as resembling two plates face to face.
interesting points: The aircraft initially appeared small but then descended a few thousand feet.
The observer reported that the aircraft hovered and maneuvered before disappearing.
The observer did not report the observation to news agencies or local authorities.
The report was sent to Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program to investigate UFOs.
The sighting involved a detailed description of the observed aircraft and the observer's interpretation of the event.
sighted object: unusual aircraft resembling two plates face to face
